HOW TO SET UP A LOCAL TESTING SERVER USING PYTHON

1st Step: Check if Python is installed

Code: python -V

2nd Step: Navigate to the directory you want to run the server

Code: cd Downloads

3rd Step: Start up the server in that directory

Code: python -m http.server

4th Step: Server is running and you may type "localhost:8000" in your browser to see the directory through HTML.
